<body>
   <p> The <b>:read-write</b> CSS pseudo-class represents an element (such as <b>&lt;input&gt;</b>Â or <b>&lt;textarea&gt;</b>) that is editable by the user. </p>
   
   <h3> Example: </h3>
   <div>
      <input type="text" value="This field is editable" />
      <input type="text" value="This field is NOT editable" readonly />
      <p contenteditable="true"> This paragraph is editable. </p>
      <p> This paragraph is NOT editable. </p>
   </div>
</body>
